===Etymology===

After Robert Sticht (1856-1922), the manager of Mount Lyell Mining and Railway Co. in Australia, in 1910.<ref>Richard V. Gaines, H. Catherine W. Skinner, Eugene E. Foord, Brian Mason, and Abraham Rosenzweig: ''Dana's new mineralogy'', John Wiley & Sons, 1997</ref>

===Noun===
'''stichtite'''

#{{mineralogy}} A [[mineral]] with [[rhombohedral]] crystals, often pink or lilac, Mg<sub>6</sub>Cr<sub>2</sub>CO<sub>3</sub>(OH)<sub>16</sub>.4H<sub>2</sub>O.

